56335 Mojave PointeBaker, CA 92309


        (760) 733-1014
    






4 for $4 real deal here. Great deal. Big hamburger  $1.99. Not great, not bad. Food was good, service was fast, lobby was clean.







Slow af, my girl ordered chicken tenders and got jalapeño poppers. When we went back inside to exchange them for the chicken tenders the guy took the jalapeño poppers put them back on the heating rack and gave her, her burnt chicken tenders. 

They took 10 minutes when I was the only one at the restaurant. I would not eat here again.







I usually look forward to Carl's Jr. on trips. This one was a major disappointment.

Bad lettuce, cheese not melted on burgers, tater tots in breakfast burger not cooked fully.

The meal tastes like a poor imitation. Luckily the fries were still good!







On our way home from visiting friends in Vegas we stopped to get lunch in Baker. We sat in the drive thru wedged in between two cars for 30 minutes. No one took our order (the speaker must have been broke) and finally the cars behind us backed out. We followed. Do not recommend.







National franchise. Clean store. Food was as expected. Server was extremely friendly and efficient. Self-serve soda machines were out of order, but I expect that they are getting them fixed. Not really much more to review.







Ignore the 1 star rating, I give this place 0 stars! 0 STARS! This place is horrible! Horrible customer service, horrible food! Rudest employees. 
BEWARE THE DRIVE THRU! I am not exaggerating, we waited in the drive thru for 50mins! Once we got to the ordering speaker the first thing the employee says to us is "Can you give us a couple of minutes?!"  
Absolutely ridiculous!







The food was good, same as any other Carl's Jr. The restaurant was clean but the bathroom needed some attention.  It was late in the day, however.







On the way home from Vegas, we stopped at Baker to get lunch to eat in the car.  The location was busy.  There were about 5 people ahead of us in line (one cashier), however, the line moved fairly fast.  

After ordering, we got our food in about 12 minutes.  It was enough time for a bathroom break and a few sips of the fountain soda, then it was back on the road towards home.  

They got my burger correct (only lettuce, tomato, and ketchup).  That doesn't always happen believe it or not!  

Service was good at Carl's Jr.  I'll be back if we are in the area (to or from Vegas).

Xie Xie!







Review for drive thru only.  Slowest drive thru ever.  Must be short staffed because they ask you to wait between each car as they assemble the prior order.  No comment as to food as I haven't received it yet but 10 minutes and 2 cars in drive thru lane is ridiculous when clearly it looks slow inside.  They should call it slow food.







They're super nice here! We ordered a turkey burger without mayo and the manager came back to suggest a sauce, in case it wasn't juicy enough without it! Thank you.







This place is a mess tonight! Trash everywhere inside of the restaurant, AC must be down because it's hot inside the seating area...and no hand-soap or towels inside the restrooms...which might mean the employees aren't washing their hands when they use the facilities. Typically this place is better than this :-(

Much better today...traveling back through and he place is perfect!!







Baker is fast food central.  Most the big guys are there.  The King, the Colonel, Jack, Subway, a Alien jerky operation, and some Greek guy with a mental disorder.  Where's the damn Clown?  No Clown!  I love the Clown and his Golden Arches!

Then you got this place.  I had forgotten my contempt for Carl's Jr.  I was lured in by the Texas BBQ Thickburger propaganda.   False advertising!  I tried one today and it was horrible!  Took two bites and threw it in the trash.

Then I bought a Crispy Chicken Sandwich with Swiss and Bacon.  Better than the Texas BBQ shit sandwich but not by much.  The salt level burned my taste buds. Thanks for the sodium.

Never going to a Carl's Jr. again.







Visited on 26 July 2015, 1640.  Since its out of the way from the main road not too much foot traffic. Jason, our cashier was professional and friendly.  Facility was not packed and clean during our visit. Minus the 106 degree weather nothing too much out of the ordinary to comment on.







What a sad turn of affairs that the amazing and iconic "Bun Boy" has been replaced by a Carl's Jr. burger. But I guess if it had to be any fast food burger to replace it - this would be a good one.

Carl's Jr. offers some fairly good burgers - even at the mouth of the Mojave Desert. So if you are sick and tired of the Gyros at The Mad Greek - come here - for curly fries, a Big Carl, and a Shake.







TERRIBLE location!!!! I can get by without coke. Maybe the manager forgot to order the syrup. However, after waiting in a long line at the drive thru. They tell me that they were out of fish as well. I was like ok it's Monday I understand. I'll just have zucchinis with ranch. Sorry sir! "We're out of ranch" well, what do you want me to dip my zucchinis in? We have BBQ and sweet and sour?  I asked him, have u dipped zucchinis in BBQ sauce. No sir! Well WTF!!!! Just over wall terrible experience. Especially when you cal rave for something and you're salivation for that taste. Just wanted to share that incase you pass thru baker.







This place is dirty.   Coffee and fountain area was dirty.  All the bins for the coffee empty and dirty.  Used the women's room and this was dirty as well.  The wash basin has a grey look to it.  The stalls have not been cleaned areas overflowing.







If I could give it no stars I would. As I write this review I'm pissed because THEY ARE OPEN. At approximately 11:23pm (yes I looked at the clock) we pulled into the parking lot of a well lit Carl's Jr. We see the male employee inside scratching his hair . We pull around and stop to look at the menu then all of a sudden everything goes dark . My husband and I are like REALLY. We pull up to see the employee doing nothing so my husband waves him over and asked if they were closed. He says "hold on bro let me check. We might can get you in" He walks and asks someone else and come and says oh sorry yeah we're closed. When clearly Yelp said they were open. As much business as I do in Vegas I will never be a patron here. #fastfoodbully. Oh and I managed to get this typed BEFORE they closed







What was I thinking coming here? I can't rate the food because we saw how trashy dirty the place was and decided, if the staff can't maintain the tables, trash and soda area, imaging the food? Place was dirty beyond anything I've ever seen..







Fine dining in Baker is limited.. Baker is our typical stop on the way or the way back from Vegas. Carl's Jr is disappointing! Quality has gone down in decades especially at this location. 

We walked in to order coming back from Vegas.. Of course I ordered my nostalgic Western Bacon Cheeseburger combo with fries and drink. The cashier said they were out of fries.. What the F! Still waiting for the stage coach to come to deliver fries. We were forced to order from the premium options which they were out of sweet potato fries and wedge cut potatoes also. I opted for the onion rings where were overcooked and disappointing. 

This location was semi clean. Not sure why it wasn't. There were barely any customers. 

I miss the charbroiled burgers which are non existent these days at Carl's Jr. If Cal was around, he'd be disappointed.







I have to say, this is a normal Carl's Junior; however. It's 11:00pm at night and we stopped with our two kids and the indoor dining was open and clean. It was really slow, but staff was busy cleaning. The food was fresh and warm. Typical Carl's junior. My stars are mostly because it was very clean, well decorated and staff was great to my kiddos. Our one year old needed to get out of the car. I wasn't terrified letting her walk around the restraunt. I got no dirty looks when she threw ice and fries on the freshly mopped floor.  Not many people show this kind of tolerance at a rest stop fast food place late at night. It was a welcomed surprise.







