        12/2/2014
    








            Listed in Yelp 100 Challenge - 2014


Fine dining in Baker is limited.. Baker is our typical stop on the way or the way back from Vegas. Carl's Jr is disappointing! Quality has gone down in decades especially at this location. We walked in to order coming back from Vegas.. Of course I ordered my nostalgic Western Bacon Cheeseburger combo with fries and drink. The cashier said they were out of fries.. What the F! Still waiting for the stage coach to come to deliver fries. We were forced to order from the premium options which they were out of sweet potato fries and wedge cut potatoes also. I opted for the onion rings where were overcooked and disappointing. This location was semi clean. Not sure why it wasn't. There were barely any customers. I miss the charbroiled burgers which are non existent these days at Carl's Jr. If Cal was around, he'd be disappointed.




