56335 Mojave PointeBaker, CA 92309


        (760) 733-1014
    






They're super nice here! We ordered a turkey burger without mayo and the manager came back to suggest a sauce, in case it wasn't juicy enough without it! Thank you.







Stopped on the way to Vegas and it was empty. One kid running the show. He handled it well food came out normal amount of time and was hot. Tasted like Carl's JR. Stopped on the way home too, same kid working (he had others this time helping) but some want to be scary guy with last weeks food stuck in he's rancid beard was yelling at the poor kid over a breakfast burrito. Poor kid looked like he had been through this song and dance before. I know people are heading home from a long weekend, hung over, broke, or what ever... But it's food people. They are doing their best. This kid did better than that. He even put up with me talking to someone while ordering. The food came out wrong because of ME! I could complain but why? There needs to be more positivity. We went to Carl's Jr. We got Carl's Jr. The staff did their job, the place was clean, what more do you need!







Clean lobby & bathrooms, nice and very polite staff and good on the road food. We ate there as a family after driving from Disneyland and the food came out quick and hot. I would stop here over any other place in town.







This Carl's Jr was spotless!  I was very impressed to see if the employees weren't helping with a customer they were cleaning. All the employees were very nice and knowledgeable of the menu.







Carl's Jr. Is located near the intersection of highway 15 and route 127.  Highway 15 is a major thoroughfare that takes you from Barstow to Lost Wages.  Route 127 is a less-traveled backroads highway that takes you to the southern and eastern entrances of Death Valley National Park.  I have visited Death Valley National Park on six different weekends, in the years 2013-2014, and found Carl's Jr. to be a welcome pit stop after a long day of hiking and photography.   I always order the Carl's Jr. Santa Fe chicken sandwich, and typically I always pay extra for additional roasted green chiles.  Because of the energy-draining quality of hiking and doing photography for eight straight hours, and because of their delicious nature, I sometimes order TWO Santa Fe chicken sandwiches.  Mmmm, I do like them. 

Carl's Jr. In Baker, CA is clean, and has polite and service-oriented cashiers.  I am also glad that Carl's Jr. In Baker, CA has good cell phone reception, since I like to call my better half after completing my long day of exploring and hiking.  After my weekend desert photography weekends, I have also gone to Carl's Jr. in Ridgecrest, CA and in Joshua Tree, CA, and always order Santa Fe chicken, with extra roasted green chiles.  

THE MAD GREEK.  An alternative to Carl's Jr. in Baker, CA is The Mad Greek.  The Mad Greek is also located at the same intersection of Route 15 and Route 127, but I think that one visit to The Mad Greek is enough.   The Mad Greek is distinguished by its amusing tacky decor (plenty of faux Greek statues), but the cuisine is not perfect (the dolmas are soggy).  And so, I tend to opt for Carl's Jr. when returning home from Death Valley, but once I stopped in Barstow at a Subway restaurant.

CARL'S JR. COFFEE.   Also, the coffee at Carl's Jr. is good.  The coffee is MUCH BETTER than that from Starbucks (blech, yech, ewww) but not as good as the coffee from Peet's.  Good coffee is important, because it takes me six hours of driving at night to return home, and generally I'm on the road until nearly midnight after my long days in the desert.







I have to say, this is a normal Carl's Junior; however. It's 11:00pm at night and we stopped with our two kids and the indoor dining was open and clean. It was really slow, but staff was busy cleaning. The food was fresh and warm. Typical Carl's junior. My stars are mostly because it was very clean, well decorated and staff was great to my kiddos. Our one year old needed to get out of the car. I wasn't terrified letting her walk around the restraunt. I got no dirty looks when she threw ice and fries on the freshly mopped floor.  Not many people show this kind of tolerance at a rest stop fast food place late at night. It was a welcomed surprise.







We went there today and a WONDERFUL NICE girl made it nice. Now we just had drive they but she was SO SO nice. She had beautiful eyelashes and tattoos. Very nice place to stop. Food was fresh. Service was perfect.







Visited on 26 July 2015, 1640.  Since its out of the way from the main road not too much foot traffic. Jason, our cashier was professional and friendly.  Facility was not packed and clean during our visit. Minus the 106 degree weather nothing too much out of the ordinary to comment on.







We moved to Vegas 3 years ago and we stopped in baker very often and everything had a "baker taste" we have not stopped in over 2 years but today the freeway was at a standstill and found the fast food place with as many stars as possible and we were surprised. when I say 5 stars it is 5 stars for Baker







I have said it before and I will say it again. I love Carl's JR burgers. I know most people prefer an InNOut but Carl's JR is where I go when I want a burger quick and conveniently. Still, I would not normally give them a 5 star review.

This location is in Baker, we were here around sunset and it was eerily quiet and lots of crows. Spooky even.

The reasons this one gets a 5 star review? The staff were friendly, the place was clean, the food was cooked perfectly, the burgers didnt fall apart and when I went to throw out my cup they reminded me that I could get a refill to go. 

They certainly went above and beyond expectations...!







4 for $4 real deal here. Great deal. Big hamburger  $1.99. Not great, not bad. Food was good, service was fast, lobby was clean.







This place is a mess tonight! Trash everywhere inside of the restaurant, AC must be down because it's hot inside the seating area...and no hand-soap or towels inside the restrooms...which might mean the employees aren't washing their hands when they use the facilities. Typically this place is better than this :-(

Much better today...traveling back through and he place is perfect!!







What can i say, its a Carls Jr.....however, it was very clean...restrooms included...i accidentally walked into the men's restroom. The greeting we received from employee, Noe was great. He was definitely happy to be there and working. He was funny, friendly and welcoming. My breakfast biscuit was tasty and the coffee was fresh, what else can you ask for. 

The Baker Carl's Jr get 2 thumbs up!!







On the way home from Vegas, we stopped at Baker to get lunch to eat in the car.  The location was busy.  There were about 5 people ahead of us in line (one cashier), however, the line moved fairly fast.  

After ordering, we got our food in about 12 minutes.  It was enough time for a bathroom break and a few sips of the fountain soda, then it was back on the road towards home.  

They got my burger correct (only lettuce, tomato, and ketchup).  That doesn't always happen believe it or not!  

Service was good at Carl's Jr.  I'll be back if we are in the area (to or from Vegas).

Xie Xie!







Tractor trailer parking /clean restrooms / fresh food. Always ask for a fresh bun for your sandwich. The sesame buns don't cut it.  10% off for truckers big deal.  Bring your coupons to make it count.







I don't know if it was the fact that I had driven for 200 miles prior to this Carl's Jr. or if they really are above the average Jr. but the Famous Star with Cheese I had was delicious. I doubt I'll become a regular though with it being about 100 miles from home.







How can you hate on Carl's? It's the best fast food joint. Stand outside and smell charbroiled burgers cookin and you'll be like "damn!" This is a new location so it's still clean and the bathrooms haven't been tagged up yet.







Clean place and very quick service. Ordered and served in 25 seconds. Chicken strips with BBQ sauce was great!







Friendly service, greeted upon entry. Food brought to table after ordering at counter & they brought ketchup and ranch without even being asked...sweet.







We stopped by this Carl's Jr. on a recent road trip. My boy wanted the chicken stars, so in we went.

We were greeted right away by the guy behind the counter, even as he was helping another customer. 

Our first stop was to the restroom to wash hands and we found it to be well kept and well stocked.

The same guy who greeted us took our order. He was very polite. I so want to give him props, but I never got around to reading the name on his badge.

Overall... Food is typical. We ordered a kids meal and a salad. I'm so glad they didn't mess it up. Place is well kept. It wasn't busy when we were there, and it was pretty quiet inside with country music playing in the background. 

Before we left, Nice Dude took our tray and trash from the table. He even checked up on us during our meal. 

Anyway... Our visit there was on Thursday, March 1, 2012 around 11am. The guy working there was super nice, really attentive, and made for a pleasant visit. I'm adding a star because of him.







