        3/4/2012
    








1 check-in
        


We stopped by this Carl's Jr. on a recent road trip. My boy wanted the chicken stars, so in we went.We were greeted right away by the guy behind the counter, even as he was helping another customer. Our first stop was to the restroom to wash hands and we found it to be well kept and well stocked.The same guy who greeted us took our order. He was very polite. I so want to give him props, but I never got around to reading the name on his badge.Overall... Food is typical. We ordered a kids meal and a salad. I'm so glad they didn't mess it up. Place is well kept. It wasn't busy when we were there, and it was pretty quiet inside with country music playing in the background. Before we left, Nice Dude took our tray and trash from the table. He even checked up on us during our meal. Anyway... Our visit there was on Thursday, March 1, 2012 around 11am. The guy working there was super nice, really attentive, and made for a pleasant visit. I'm adding a star because of him.








