        5/29/2013
    








1 check-in
        









            Listed in Yelp Year 2013, SoCal Cruising


Well this is just your average Carl's Jr.  It looked ok and had the same quality that you expect from other Carl's Jr stores.  The burgers we ordered were yummy and the fries were fresh.  The reason I gave this location 2 stars is because of the women's restroom.  This may sound bad, but Baker, CA is a pit stop for almost everyone that passes through it for restroom breaks between Las Vegas and LA.  Every place in this town should have a clean restroom.  Well this fact was missed on this Carl's Jr.  The women's restroom smelled of urine (now that gets my appetite going!), had messy stalls, and a pile of dirty diapers next to the changing table.  If the bathroom was clean, I definitely would have given this place a solid 3 maybe a 4 star rating.




